¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Definition} ⦉

  ‖ Let $p: ∏_{i = 1}^{n} A_i → 𝗥$ be a distribution on $A$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ For $i ≠ j ∈ \set{1, …, n}$, the ❬conditional distribution❭
    of $i$ on $j$ is the function $p_{i | j}: A_i × A_j → 𝗥$
    defined so that that $p_{i | j}(\cdot, b)$ is the
    conditional distribution induced by conditioning on $\Set{a ∈
    ∏_{i = 1}^{n} A_i }{a_j = b}$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ For $i,j = 1, …, n$ and $i ≠ j$, $p_i$ and $p_{i,j}$
    satisify
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p_{i | j}(b, c)p_{j}(c) = p_{ij}(b, c) ⦉
    ⦉
    for $b ∈ A_i$ and $c ∈ A_j$. ⦉
⦉

